HEADWORD: Deodate
<hw>De"o*date`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>Deo</ets>
to God (<ets>Deus</ets> God) + <ets>datum</ets> thing given.]</ety>
<def>A gift or offering to God.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wherein that blessed widow's <qex>deodate</qex> was laid up.</q>
<rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

